WEBVTT

00:01.830 --> 00:04.710
[ Rain falling ]

00:12.880 --> 00:14.960
[ Door clanking ]

00:20.500 --> 00:22.750
You're not going to
investigate, are you?

00:22.750 --> 00:25.210
I'm too compromised.

00:25.210 --> 00:27.000
I'd be a liability.

00:27.000 --> 00:29.170
Why drag me out here
in the middle of the night

00:29.170 --> 00:30.960
if you're not even gonna --
You know what?

00:30.960 --> 00:33.620
Never mind. You've already
wasted too much of my time.

00:33.620 --> 00:35.830
Ms. Pope.

00:35.830 --> 00:38.380
What if I can get you
a Senate hearing?

00:38.380 --> 00:41.330
Something with scope,
resources.

00:41.330 --> 00:45.120
♪♪

00:45.120 --> 00:46.750
Can you make that
happen?

00:46.750 --> 00:50.040
I can...

00:50.040 --> 00:51.500
but I need you to make me
a promise.

00:51.500 --> 00:53.210
♪♪

00:53.210 --> 00:55.170
I need you to guarantee

00:55.170 --> 00:57.330
that if Mellie Grant
stays President,

00:57.330 --> 00:59.540
she'll make gun control
a priority.

00:59.540 --> 01:01.120
Gun control?

01:01.120 --> 01:02.460
Gun control.

01:02.460 --> 01:05.210
If Jake Ballard
and Cyrus Beene go to jail

01:05.210 --> 01:07.250
and B613
is gotten rid of,

01:07.250 --> 01:09.920
yes, I can promise you
that gun control will move

01:09.920 --> 01:12.380
to the top of the Grant
administration agenda.

01:12.380 --> 01:14.420
♪♪

01:14.420 --> 01:16.620
Thank you.

01:16.620 --> 01:19.750
♪♪

01:19.750 --> 01:21.290
What are you doing?

01:21.290 --> 01:22.580
I'm getting you
your Senate hearing.

01:22.580 --> 01:23.580
No, Lonnie!

01:23.580 --> 01:24.620
[ Gunshot ]

01:24.620 --> 01:26.960
[ Gasping ]

01:29.210 --> 01:32.750
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

01:32.750 --> 01:37.290
Liberty Lovers, our brethren
in the U.S. Senate

01:37.290 --> 01:40.830
have just this morning
formed a select committee --

01:40.830 --> 01:45.330
the sole purpose of which is
to investigate B613.

01:45.330 --> 01:48.580
Sadly, it took the suicide
of Mr. Lonnie Mencken

01:48.580 --> 01:50.210
to make this happen.

01:50.210 --> 01:52.540
Mencken's death sent shock
waves through the capital,

01:52.540 --> 01:54.580
confirming once and for all

01:54.580 --> 01:58.170
that we've got rats
in our nation's basements.

01:58.170 --> 02:00.330
Fear no more, Liberty Lovers.

02:00.330 --> 02:03.000
Mama's calling
the exterminator.

02:03.000 --> 02:05.040
It's killing time.

02:05.040 --> 02:06.960
The questions raised
by Sally Langston

02:06.960 --> 02:09.290
and the death of Lonnie Mencken
are very serious questions.

02:09.290 --> 02:10.620
As head of
the select committee,

02:10.620 --> 02:13.500
it is my sworn duty to get
America some answers.

02:13.500 --> 02:16.500
Now, if that means questioning
old political rivals, so be it.

02:16.500 --> 02:18.380
We need to create
kill folders

02:18.380 --> 02:20.580
on every single member
of that committee.

02:20.580 --> 02:22.420
What are you so worked up about?
Lonnie's dead.

02:22.420 --> 02:24.120
His conscience won't be
a problem anymore.

02:24.120 --> 02:25.170
The select committee --

02:25.170 --> 02:26.500
The select committee
has no teeth

02:26.500 --> 02:28.380
without the backing
of the Justice Department.

02:28.380 --> 02:30.250
Jake, who runs
the Justice Department?!

02:33.460 --> 02:36.290
No. No, he had to
recuse himself.

02:36.290 --> 02:38.380
That's the old
playing field.

02:38.380 --> 02:40.580
This is a brand-new game
we're playing.

02:40.580 --> 02:42.750
It's not just about
the hijacking anymore.

02:42.750 --> 02:44.250
It's about B613,
which means --

02:44.250 --> 02:45.750
David Rosen
is back in charge.

02:45.750 --> 02:48.330
That's why
I'm so worked up.

02:48.330 --> 02:51.120
They've scheduled a closed-door
session tomorrow.

02:51.120 --> 02:52.580
You and everyone else
they've subpoenaed

02:52.580 --> 02:54.250
will testify before
the committee's 15 members.

02:54.250 --> 02:55.750
Once everyone's been
questioned,

02:55.750 --> 02:57.290
they'll make
the recommendations to me

02:57.290 --> 02:58.500
as to which charges
should be filed.

02:58.500 --> 03:00.380
We'll keep our answers
short and straightforward.

03:00.380 --> 03:02.250
1/10th of what we know
should be enough

03:02.250 --> 03:03.420
to force them
to take on B613.

03:03.420 --> 03:04.620
What happens
to Jake and Cyrus?

03:04.620 --> 03:06.920
Exposing B613 means exposing
Jake and Cyrus, so...

03:06.920 --> 03:08.330
So they're screwed?

03:08.330 --> 03:10.710
Not a legal term, but, yes,
they will be screwed.

03:10.710 --> 03:12.290
And the rest of us?

03:12.290 --> 03:13.790
We're confessing
to some bad things --

03:13.790 --> 03:15.750
some of those things
really bad.

03:15.750 --> 03:18.670
Like really, really bad.

03:18.670 --> 03:20.670
Does that mean
we're screwed, too?

03:20.670 --> 03:25.250
♪♪

03:25.250 --> 03:30.420
♪♪

03:30.420 --> 03:33.620
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

03:33.620 --> 03:36.000
[ Gulls calling ]

03:36.000 --> 03:37.830
Why did you
summon me here?

03:37.830 --> 03:40.540
I'm the one.

03:40.540 --> 03:44.040
I exposed B613, Sally Langston,
the committee...

03:44.040 --> 03:45.500
That all started
with me.

03:45.500 --> 03:47.960
Hmm.

03:47.960 --> 03:50.620
Then now you're
going to testify?

03:50.620 --> 03:52.210
Yes.

03:52.210 --> 03:53.830
-Do you want my blessing?
-No...

03:53.830 --> 03:55.250
-[ Chuckling ] Good.
-...I want your help.

03:55.250 --> 03:57.750
-Ha! My help. [ Laughs ]
-You can join us.

03:57.750 --> 03:59.380
You can be on
the right side of this.

03:59.380 --> 04:01.120
You can help hand this country
back to the people.

04:03.420 --> 04:04.710
What's this?

04:04.710 --> 04:06.380
The deed to my house,

04:06.380 --> 04:08.710
keys to a safety-deposit box
in Alexandria,

04:08.710 --> 04:10.920
offshore account number
for a trust I've set up

04:10.920 --> 04:12.210
for you and your child.

04:12.210 --> 04:13.920
Why are you
giving this to me?

04:13.920 --> 04:15.290
I'm leaving, Olivia.

04:15.290 --> 04:17.540
You want to fix this,
fix it yourself.

04:17.540 --> 04:20.080
What do you want
from me?

04:22.250 --> 04:24.380
This is my chance
to start over,

04:24.380 --> 04:26.080
to live in the light,
stand in my truth,

04:26.080 --> 04:27.750
and become the person
you raised --

04:27.750 --> 04:29.580
someone you could
be proud of.

04:29.580 --> 04:31.880
The person I raised
doesn't hold out her hands

04:31.880 --> 04:33.830
and smile when
she's being shackled.

04:33.830 --> 04:35.120
That's what a slave does.

04:35.120 --> 04:37.000
-Dad, y--
-Stop talking!

04:38.790 --> 04:41.460
Watching my child
enslave herself

04:41.460 --> 04:43.830
in order to fix
massa's problem,

04:43.830 --> 04:46.210
this unyielding desire
of hers

04:46.210 --> 04:49.080
to fix everybody else's
problem --

04:49.080 --> 04:52.330
What did I do wrong?

04:52.330 --> 04:53.920
What you did, Dad,

04:53.920 --> 04:55.830
was the very same thing

04:55.830 --> 04:57.710
all those years
of protecting the Republic,

04:57.710 --> 04:59.710
doing their dirty work
for their government --

04:59.710 --> 05:02.210
That was you leading
by example.

05:02.210 --> 05:03.790
So tell me,
what's the difference?

05:03.790 --> 05:05.830
It wasn't their government.
It was mine.

05:05.830 --> 05:07.500
I was in charge,
I made the rules,

05:07.500 --> 05:09.710
but I stayed
in the shadows. Why?

05:09.710 --> 05:13.080
Because in the end, they don't
care what happens to us.

05:13.080 --> 05:15.290
You think because they
pet you on the head

05:15.290 --> 05:17.170
and tell you that
you're smart and pretty

05:17.170 --> 05:19.920
that you matter to them?!

05:19.920 --> 05:22.750
You are in the light so that
they can stay in the dark.

05:22.750 --> 05:24.420
After this investigation
is over,

05:24.420 --> 05:26.380
no one will be
in the shadows.

05:26.380 --> 05:28.330
No more tricks,
no more dirty, little secrets,

05:28.330 --> 05:30.750
no more B613 --
everyone equal.

05:30.750 --> 05:33.880
And this country
will be better for it.

05:33.880 --> 05:35.250
You sure about that?

05:42.120 --> 05:44.500
[ Helicopter blades whir ]

05:52.210 --> 05:54.120
Reporter: We're live
outside the Capitol,

05:54.120 --> 05:55.330
where we're just hours away

05:55.330 --> 05:56.960
from today's closed-door
committee hearing.

05:56.960 --> 05:58.620
We don't know exactly
who's testifying,

05:58.620 --> 06:00.960
but if rumors are true, some
D.C.'s highest and mightiest

06:00.960 --> 06:05.290
have some serious explaining to
do about this so-called B613.

06:05.290 --> 06:08.580
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

06:08.580 --> 06:09.710
[ Gasps ]

06:09.710 --> 06:11.000
[ Door opens ]

06:11.000 --> 06:13.120
Madam President, I'll --

06:13.120 --> 06:14.790
Wow.

06:14.790 --> 06:17.250
With everything that's going on,
the National Portrait Gallery

06:17.250 --> 06:19.420
decided to postpone
the unveiling,

06:19.420 --> 06:23.790
so...I had them send
mine over in the meantime.

06:23.790 --> 06:24.670
It's beautiful.

06:24.670 --> 06:26.330
Isn't me.

06:26.330 --> 06:28.500
That is a portrait
of the First Lady

06:28.500 --> 06:31.040
of the United States of America
in 100 years.

06:31.040 --> 06:33.420
That's the only Mellie Grant
anyone will see.

06:33.420 --> 06:35.540
You are the President
of the United States.

06:35.540 --> 06:37.580
People will know who you are
and what you've done.

06:37.580 --> 06:39.790
They will know
I was impeached.

06:39.790 --> 06:42.750
Once I have testified,
the House will impeach me,

06:42.750 --> 06:46.170
and the Democratic Senate
will throw me out.

06:46.170 --> 06:48.830
Those are the facts.
That's the end of my story.

06:48.830 --> 06:50.540
Mellie, I --

06:50.540 --> 06:53.040
Marcus, I didn't invite you
here for a pity party.

06:53.040 --> 06:55.210
I wanted to you tell you...

06:57.250 --> 06:59.080
[ Sighs ]

07:00.830 --> 07:02.620
[ Sighs ]

07:04.830 --> 07:07.080
[ Sighs ]

07:09.210 --> 07:11.120
It's funny how much time
I've spent

07:11.120 --> 07:13.290
trying to make
all the right moves,

07:13.290 --> 07:16.250
being afraid
of making a mistake,

07:16.250 --> 07:20.750
afraid to just...

07:20.750 --> 07:23.460
be here...

07:23.460 --> 07:25.250
with you.

07:36.920 --> 07:38.750
[ Clears throat ]

07:41.380 --> 07:43.250
[ Gasps ]
Oh, my God.

07:43.250 --> 07:45.500
There, it's straight.

07:45.500 --> 07:46.920
Thanks.

07:46.920 --> 07:47.920
Quinn --

07:47.920 --> 07:49.330
I have a baby.

07:49.330 --> 07:51.460
I'm voluntarily marching
myself into prison,

07:51.460 --> 07:53.670
and my baby hasn't even
taken her first steps yet,

07:53.670 --> 07:55.500
spoken her first word.
I'm gonna miss it --

07:55.500 --> 07:56.920
all of it.

07:56.920 --> 07:58.960
Robin's about to grow up
with a couple cons for parents.

07:58.960 --> 08:00.880
I watch enough reality TV.
I know how that turns out.

08:00.880 --> 08:03.170
That's why you're doing this.
You're doing this for Robin

08:03.170 --> 08:04.080
so that she --
-Shut up!

08:06.120 --> 08:09.290
Look, I'm sorry,
but seriously, I mean, shut up.

08:09.290 --> 08:11.170
I don't need to be
talked into it.

08:11.170 --> 08:12.750
I'm in...clearly.

08:12.750 --> 08:16.290
I just...I'm scared.
I need Charlie.

08:16.290 --> 08:17.960
He doesn't even know
I'm doing this.

08:17.960 --> 08:20.830
At least you don't have to worry
about him ever leaving you

08:20.830 --> 08:22.670
or moving onto someone,
you know, not in jail.

08:22.670 --> 08:24.460
Moving on?
What are you talking about?

08:24.460 --> 08:26.000
I'm sure you'll be
nice at first,

08:26.000 --> 08:28.330
but what about a few months when
I'm covered in prison tats

08:28.330 --> 08:29.620
and you're tired
of talking to me

08:29.620 --> 08:31.290
through a thick pane
of bulletproof glass?

08:31.290 --> 08:33.120
You'll start visiting
once a week,

08:33.120 --> 08:35.250
then only on my birthday,
and then not at all.

08:35.250 --> 08:37.380
And one day, I'll read
you married Jennifer,

08:37.380 --> 08:39.120
a nice Jewish girl
your nana just loves.

08:39.120 --> 08:41.210
I have to talk
in front of 15 people!

08:45.750 --> 08:47.040
[ Cellphone chimes ]

08:47.040 --> 08:49.250
The cars are here.

08:49.250 --> 08:54.120
♪♪

08:54.120 --> 08:55.540
[ Gavel pounds ]

08:55.540 --> 08:57.460
The Select Committee
will proceed now

08:57.460 --> 08:59.330
with the first witness
in our inquiry

08:59.330 --> 09:01.790
into the existence
and activity

09:01.790 --> 09:04.500
of government agency B-6-1-3.

09:04.500 --> 09:06.710
Will you please state
your name for the record?

09:06.710 --> 09:08.500
-My name is...
-Thomas Larsen.

09:08.500 --> 09:10.670
-Diego Muñoz.
-Abby Whelan.

09:10.670 --> 09:13.080
Quinn Perkins, previously
known as Lindsay Dwyer.

09:13.080 --> 09:14.210
Fitzgerald Grant.

09:14.210 --> 09:15.210
Melody Grant.

09:15.210 --> 09:17.540
My name?
[ Chuckles ]

09:17.540 --> 09:19.670
Ain't nobody within
20 klicks of the Potomac

09:19.670 --> 09:22.080
don't know Hollis Doyle
by sight or sound.

09:22.080 --> 09:24.080
And you know
that Jake Ballard

09:24.080 --> 09:27.420
assassinated President Rashad
because you saw him do it?

09:27.420 --> 09:30.000
I know he killed Rashad
because I ordered him to do it.

09:30.000 --> 09:32.710
[ Committee members murmur ]

09:32.710 --> 09:35.500
And how many killings
were you ordered to carry out

09:35.500 --> 09:37.000
on behalf of B613?

09:37.000 --> 09:38.670
One.

09:38.670 --> 09:41.500
♪♪

09:41.500 --> 09:43.580
[ Sighs ]

09:43.580 --> 09:47.170
♪♪

09:47.170 --> 09:48.170
[ Glass clunks ]

09:48.170 --> 09:49.250
A lot.

09:49.250 --> 09:51.040
♪♪

09:51.040 --> 09:52.880
I was aware of B613, yes.

09:52.880 --> 09:55.080
Yes.

09:55.080 --> 09:56.420
That's correct.

09:56.420 --> 09:58.670
And Cyrus Beene
personally ordered you

09:58.670 --> 10:00.620
to kill
Governor Frankie Vargas?

10:00.620 --> 10:02.330
He's too smart
to leave a trail,

10:02.330 --> 10:05.830
too crafty, too...evil.

10:05.830 --> 10:07.460
Fake hijacking?

10:07.460 --> 10:09.500
Damn. That's good.

10:09.500 --> 10:11.460
Compared to that,
all I did was

10:11.460 --> 10:13.500
tilt a few pinball machines
at the arcade.

10:13.500 --> 10:15.580
Cyrus Beene staged
the hijacking of Air Force Two

10:15.580 --> 10:17.250
for his own
political benefit.

10:17.250 --> 10:18.830
Then he, along
with Jake Ballard,

10:18.830 --> 10:20.750
proceeded to frame
President Mellie Grant.

10:20.750 --> 10:22.830
Abby: There's no
evidence linking Cyrus
to the hijacking,

10:22.830 --> 10:24.710
but there is evidence
of a coverup.

10:24.710 --> 10:27.080
-...used Jake Ballard...
-...the future of everyone...

10:27.080 --> 10:29.380
I made sure that the hacker's
code trail linking Charlie...

10:29.380 --> 10:31.710
-...must be stopped.
-I plead the Fifth,

10:31.710 --> 10:34.710
the First, the Second --
hell, every damn amendment.

10:34.710 --> 10:36.750
Any further questions,
talk to my lawyer,

10:36.750 --> 10:38.580
or y'all can come find me
at the Gettysburger

10:38.580 --> 10:40.330
down on D and 8th.

10:40.330 --> 10:42.330
♪♪

10:42.330 --> 10:43.500
So what now?

10:43.500 --> 10:45.000
Now we wait.

10:45.000 --> 10:46.750
When the committee's
done deliberating,

10:46.750 --> 10:48.460
they'll reach out to me
with their recommendations.

10:48.460 --> 10:50.540
Since that could mean jail time
for some of you,

10:50.540 --> 10:52.960
I'd use the next 24 hours
to get my affairs in order

10:52.960 --> 10:54.540
and say my goodbyes.

10:54.540 --> 10:55.670
Any questions?

11:02.460 --> 11:05.420
No questions, but we do
have a favor to ask.

11:05.420 --> 11:06.790
[ Door opens ]

11:09.880 --> 11:11.080
[ Door closes ]

11:13.790 --> 11:15.540
[ Handcuffs rattle ]

11:15.540 --> 11:17.080
Come here.

11:26.460 --> 11:28.080
Uh, we -- we only have
10 minutes.

11:28.080 --> 11:29.830
-[ Panting ]
-How's Robin?

11:29.830 --> 11:32.380
Oh, she's -- she's great.

11:32.380 --> 11:33.460
She's smiling.

11:33.460 --> 11:35.330
Oh, she's smiling.
Oh, that's fantastic.

11:35.330 --> 11:37.540
I'm gonna be
executed, right?

11:37.540 --> 11:39.380
That's why you're all here?
I'm a dead man walking.

11:39.380 --> 11:40.750
No, you're not going
to be executed.

11:40.750 --> 11:42.170
[ Breathes shakily ]

11:42.170 --> 11:44.080
I testified about B613
this morning.

11:44.080 --> 11:45.460
-We all did.
-Everything's out in the open.

11:46.670 --> 11:48.040
Oh.

11:48.040 --> 11:49.500
So you're being executed.

11:49.500 --> 11:51.330
No one's being executed.
Not today at least.

11:51.330 --> 11:53.460
Just shut up
and let me marry you.

11:53.460 --> 11:55.920
Okay, this might be
our last chance

11:55.920 --> 11:57.330
to make it official --
you and me.

11:57.330 --> 11:59.080
So...

11:59.080 --> 12:00.620
what do you say?

12:03.000 --> 12:04.500
Will you marry me?

12:04.500 --> 12:06.000
[ Stevie Wonder's
"For Once in My Life" plays ]

12:06.000 --> 12:08.000
I see. Yes.

12:08.000 --> 12:09.670
Of course, yes!

12:09.670 --> 12:11.120
Okay.

12:11.120 --> 12:13.670
♪ Someone I've needed so long ♪

12:13.670 --> 12:16.620
-Dearly beloved, we --
-Wait, is this gonna be offish?

12:16.620 --> 12:19.880
Yes.
I registered online.

12:19.880 --> 12:23.120
Um, we are gathered here today
to witness the union

12:23.120 --> 12:25.920
of two people whose love
for each other

12:25.920 --> 12:28.580
has been an inspiration
to all of us.

12:28.580 --> 12:31.040
Do you --
legal name, please.

12:31.040 --> 12:33.170
Charlie's fine.

12:33.170 --> 12:35.830
♪ Oh, someone more like you ♪

12:35.830 --> 12:37.830
Bernard.

12:37.830 --> 12:39.380
Bernard Gusky.

12:39.380 --> 12:40.710
♪ Yeah, yeah ♪

12:40.710 --> 12:41.830
Your name's Bernard?

12:41.830 --> 12:43.210
It's a family name.

12:43.210 --> 12:44.790
It's a good name.

12:44.790 --> 12:46.790
♪♪

12:46.790 --> 12:50.000
And do you, Bernard, take Quinn
to be your lawfully-wedded wife?

12:50.000 --> 12:52.210
I do.

12:52.210 --> 12:54.750
You're not Robin, Quinn.

12:54.750 --> 12:55.920
♪♪

12:55.920 --> 12:57.750
You're Batman.

12:57.750 --> 13:00.000
♪♪

13:00.000 --> 13:02.880
[ Shakily ] Do you, Quinn,
take Bernard

13:02.880 --> 13:04.420
to be your lawfully-wedded
husband?

13:04.420 --> 13:06.460
I do.

13:06.460 --> 13:09.500
And I promise to never
hack you without cause,

13:09.500 --> 13:12.380
to help you hide the bodies,
no questions asked,

13:12.380 --> 13:16.000
and to always
have your six

13:16.000 --> 13:18.080
till the day
I die for real.

13:18.080 --> 13:19.290
[ Sighs ]

13:19.290 --> 13:21.790
By the power vested in me,

13:21.790 --> 13:25.750
it my great honor to pronounce
you husband and wife.

13:25.750 --> 13:27.920
You may kiss the bride.

13:27.920 --> 13:29.210
[ Chuckles ]

13:29.210 --> 13:32.670
♪♪

13:32.670 --> 13:38.500
[ Applause ]

13:38.500 --> 13:41.000
David: Bernard? Really?
[ Chuckling ]

13:41.000 --> 13:43.120
How did Huck do?

13:43.120 --> 13:46.080
No, I'm not jealous,
I'm just sad that I missed it.

13:48.790 --> 13:50.920
Abby, I'll call you back.

13:52.880 --> 13:54.420
You look happy.

13:54.420 --> 13:55.710
That's unfortunate.

13:55.710 --> 13:58.670
The sky is falling --
literally falling --

13:58.670 --> 14:00.960
and you are...happy.

14:00.960 --> 14:03.960
One, the sky isn't literally
falling because if --

14:03.960 --> 14:05.380
Whatever.

14:05.380 --> 14:08.920
Two, I'm just doing
my job.

14:08.920 --> 14:10.920
I always liked you, David.

14:10.920 --> 14:12.500
You seem smart.

14:12.500 --> 14:15.380
You're not gonna flatter me
into sparing you.

14:15.380 --> 14:17.710
I'm not being literal.

14:17.710 --> 14:20.040
I'm threatening you.

14:20.040 --> 14:22.080
Imagine the gun
in my waistband

14:22.080 --> 14:24.080
was no longer
in my waistband --

14:24.080 --> 14:25.750
it was pointing
at your head.

14:25.750 --> 14:27.460
Familiar?

14:27.460 --> 14:30.880
And I say something like,
"I always liked you, David.

14:30.880 --> 14:32.670
You seem smart."

14:33.750 --> 14:35.330
Yeah. That's it.

14:35.330 --> 14:38.000
That's the look I remember
after I shot your pal, James.

14:38.000 --> 14:40.170
Then I ask one more time,

14:40.170 --> 14:42.460
"Are you smart, David?"

14:44.790 --> 14:48.290
♪♪

14:48.290 --> 14:52.040
♪♪

14:52.040 --> 14:53.460
What are you doing?

14:53.460 --> 14:54.960
Not giving in...

14:54.960 --> 14:57.170
not backing down,
not running.

14:57.170 --> 14:59.880
You're not gonna shoot me in the
back like you did James Novak.

14:59.880 --> 15:02.330
I'd prefer you didn't
shoot me in the face.

15:02.330 --> 15:04.080
Believe it or not,
I'm kind of vain,

15:04.080 --> 15:06.210
but I can only control
what I can control.

15:06.210 --> 15:08.000
-Are you ready to die?
-No! What?!

15:08.000 --> 15:10.330
What kind of crazy person
is ready to die?!

15:10.330 --> 15:11.790
I'm just...

15:11.790 --> 15:13.830
I'm just sick of all this.

15:13.830 --> 15:17.000
And I'm supposed to cry and run
because I'm your bitch?

15:17.000 --> 15:19.880
But I'm not your bitch,
Jake Ballard.

15:19.880 --> 15:24.250
I...am...not...your...bitch!

15:24.250 --> 15:27.040
I'm the Attorney General
of the United States.

15:27.040 --> 15:29.670
I'm the bitch of
the United States of America,

15:29.670 --> 15:31.080
and this is me
acting like it.

15:31.080 --> 15:32.880
You sound ridiculous.

15:32.880 --> 15:34.620
Why would you get it?

15:34.620 --> 15:37.080
What do you stand for?
What do you care about?

15:37.080 --> 15:38.790
W-W-- Who cares
about you, huh?

15:38.790 --> 15:40.670
Seriously, who cares about you?
Who would miss you?

15:40.670 --> 15:41.670
Shut up, Rosen.

15:41.670 --> 15:43.420
People will miss me.
They care about me.

15:43.420 --> 15:45.290
There are people
out there that I love.

15:45.290 --> 15:47.080
What do you love?
Who do you love?

15:47.080 --> 15:48.380
Shut up!

15:48.380 --> 15:49.960
You know what you are?

15:49.960 --> 15:51.620
You're the bitch.

15:51.620 --> 15:52.880
You're always
someone's bitch.

15:52.880 --> 15:54.710
This time it's
Cyrus Rutherford Beene.

15:54.710 --> 15:56.960
So go ahead.

15:56.960 --> 15:58.960
Do what Daddy
told you to do.

15:58.960 --> 16:00.380
[ Gun cocks ]

16:00.380 --> 16:03.750
♪♪

16:03.750 --> 16:06.790
Or...you could try on
the white hat.

16:06.790 --> 16:09.000
For the first time in your life,
you could see how it feels.

16:09.000 --> 16:10.830
You could decide to care
about something

16:10.830 --> 16:13.420
for no other reason than because
it's the right thing to do.

16:13.420 --> 16:16.670
♪♪

16:16.670 --> 16:20.580
♪♪

16:20.580 --> 16:23.540
♪♪

16:23.540 --> 16:25.460
I'm grabbing my stuff.

16:25.460 --> 16:31.210
♪♪

16:31.210 --> 16:33.250
I'm leaving.

16:33.250 --> 16:34.790
So whatever.

16:34.790 --> 16:36.790
Shoot me in the back
if you really want.

16:36.790 --> 16:38.620
It's kind of your thing,
I guess.

16:38.620 --> 16:43.330
♪♪

16:43.330 --> 16:48.000
♪♪

16:48.000 --> 16:53.000
♪♪

16:59.120 --> 17:00.750
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

17:02.750 --> 17:05.040
[ Door opens ]

17:05.040 --> 17:07.330
So... [ Sighs ]

17:07.330 --> 17:08.540
So what?

17:08.540 --> 17:10.830
Did you pay
our little friend a visit?

17:10.830 --> 17:13.210
I went to see Rosen, yeah.

17:13.210 --> 17:15.000
And?

17:15.000 --> 17:17.920
[ Sighs ]
And I'm going home.

17:17.920 --> 17:20.080
I'm sorry?

17:20.080 --> 17:22.170
Did you really not hear
what I said?

17:22.170 --> 17:23.500
I'm confused.

17:23.500 --> 17:26.210
Did you take care of
our David Rosen problem or not?

17:29.420 --> 17:30.750
Ballard?!

17:30.750 --> 17:32.500
Get your hand off me.

17:32.500 --> 17:34.670
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:38.380 --> 17:40.380
You couldn't do it?
You backed down?

17:40.380 --> 17:43.710
You couldn't man up?

17:43.710 --> 17:46.920
The committee makes its
recommendation tomorrow,

17:46.920 --> 17:49.670
and if David Rosen is
still our Attorney General

17:49.670 --> 17:52.000
when that happens,
we're finished.

17:52.000 --> 17:53.460
Is that what you want?

17:53.460 --> 17:55.500
[ Quietly ] I kill.

17:55.500 --> 17:57.670
I am a killer.

17:57.670 --> 17:59.290
I could kill David Rosen

17:59.290 --> 18:02.290
and not lose one second
of sleep, but for what -- you?

18:02.290 --> 18:04.670
You can't do what I've done.
You think you're a killer,

18:04.670 --> 18:07.040
but you've never actually
gotten your hands dirty.

18:07.040 --> 18:08.790
Without me, you're
just a whiny seal

18:08.790 --> 18:10.830
barking orders
from behind a desk.

18:10.830 --> 18:14.120
So until you actually
put a bullet in someone's head

18:14.120 --> 18:17.380
or snap someone's neck while
they breathed their last breath

18:17.380 --> 18:20.580
through your fingers,
don't ever question me.

18:23.210 --> 18:28.120
Now, like I said,
I'm going home.

18:31.460 --> 18:33.830
[ Door opens ]

18:33.830 --> 18:36.460
[ Door closes ]

18:36.460 --> 18:39.380
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

18:39.380 --> 18:41.710
I never stand up
to anyone...ever.

18:41.710 --> 18:45.460
I'm a lawyer. I'm too worried
about the legal ramifications,

18:45.460 --> 18:48.670
but standing up to Jake,
looking death in the eye

18:48.670 --> 18:52.250
and walking away from it,
that felt so good.

18:52.250 --> 18:54.210
What time do you think
the committee

18:54.210 --> 18:56.290
will issue
its recommendation?

18:56.290 --> 18:58.420
I could have the recommendation
in my hand by lunch.

18:58.420 --> 19:00.920
Lunch. Right. Good.

19:00.920 --> 19:04.460
So...I'll be in prison
by when exactly?

19:06.750 --> 19:08.620
I will never leave you.
Okay?

19:08.620 --> 19:11.710
I will never marry a nice
Jewish girl named Jennifer.

19:11.710 --> 19:14.080
I will wait for you.

19:14.080 --> 19:16.170
I will wait
as long as it takes.

19:22.380 --> 19:24.420
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

19:28.790 --> 19:30.000
What is it?

19:30.000 --> 19:33.170
Cyrus.
He wants to deal.

19:33.170 --> 19:36.750
♪♪

19:36.750 --> 19:38.750
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

19:38.750 --> 19:40.170
David:
I'll enter this confession

19:40.170 --> 19:41.710
into the official record
in the morning.

19:41.710 --> 19:44.420
You're prepared to admit
that you hijacked Air Force Two

19:44.420 --> 19:46.500
and framed President
Mellie Grant for the crime?

19:46.500 --> 19:48.920
Among other things, yes.

19:48.920 --> 19:50.830
[ Sighs ]
You want a drink?

19:50.830 --> 19:52.460
Have a drink with me.

19:52.460 --> 19:53.670
I'd rather not.

19:53.670 --> 19:55.710
Oh, come on, Rosen.
[ Chuckles ]

19:55.710 --> 19:57.670
This is the end
of the road for me,

19:57.670 --> 20:00.080
and when we're done here, you're
going to have me arrested.

20:00.080 --> 20:01.210
Fine.

20:04.750 --> 20:06.330
[ Sighs ]

20:06.330 --> 20:08.420
I'm not a bad person,
Rosen.

20:08.420 --> 20:10.880
I wouldn't say
you're a good person.

20:10.880 --> 20:13.380
[ Liquid pours ]
God, I've never
really understood the...

20:13.380 --> 20:15.380
value of good people.

20:17.830 --> 20:19.500
Too many good people
are just people

20:19.500 --> 20:23.290
without goals,
drive, will.

20:23.290 --> 20:25.080
[ Glasses clink ]

20:26.710 --> 20:30.620
I'm not
a good person, but...

20:30.620 --> 20:34.920
there is [sniffs] a reason
for everything I do,

20:34.920 --> 20:36.960
and it may be sick
and twisted to some,

20:36.960 --> 20:41.170
but...it is always
thought out,

20:41.170 --> 20:44.210
never executed out of...

20:44.210 --> 20:46.460
spite or malice,
never hasty.

20:46.460 --> 20:48.040
Okay.

20:48.040 --> 20:51.170
I'm consistent.
I do what needs to be done.

20:51.170 --> 20:54.250
I-I do what
other people can't.

20:54.250 --> 20:56.210
I am relentless...
-[ Coughs ]

20:56.210 --> 20:58.170
...in pursuit
of the things I want,

20:58.170 --> 21:00.580
and I will not let anyone
stand in my way.

21:00.580 --> 21:03.290
And sometimes
people get hurt.

21:03.290 --> 21:05.620
I am inches away
from the Oval.

21:05.620 --> 21:07.620
I can taste my dream.

21:07.620 --> 21:10.500
And you...

21:10.500 --> 21:11.960
[ Snorts ]

21:11.960 --> 21:15.790
...David Rosen, you...

21:15.790 --> 21:17.290
are in my way.

21:17.290 --> 21:19.330
No hard feelings.

21:22.170 --> 21:24.380
[ Groaning ]

21:24.380 --> 21:27.420
[ Choking, gasping ]

21:33.620 --> 21:36.000
[ Gasping continues ]

21:47.120 --> 21:49.830
[ Breathing raggedly ]

21:56.380 --> 21:58.830
[ Muffled screaming ]

22:00.580 --> 22:02.710
[ Breathing heavily ]

22:06.880 --> 22:08.120
[ Struggling stops ]

22:30.580 --> 22:33.120
[ Gasps ]

22:43.670 --> 22:44.960
[ Quietly ] Help.

22:47.380 --> 22:48.710
[ Normal voice ] Help.

22:48.710 --> 22:49.710
Help!

23:02.710 --> 23:05.080
They said it was
a heart attack.

23:07.380 --> 23:10.830
It was Cyrus...and Jake.

23:10.830 --> 23:13.250
But why was he even
at the Naval Observatory?

23:13.250 --> 23:15.210
You don't just go meet
with the enemy

23:15.210 --> 23:16.880
you're threatening
to take down.

23:16.880 --> 23:19.040
Cyrus told him
he wanted to cooperate.

23:19.040 --> 23:20.790
It was a trap.

23:28.210 --> 23:30.750
So...that's it?

23:32.790 --> 23:36.210
The monsters win?
Long live the monsters?

23:36.210 --> 23:38.790
I mean, what else
can we do?

23:38.790 --> 23:41.790
Charlie's still in custody and
the one good guy left is dead.

23:41.790 --> 23:44.880
David...is dead.

23:44.880 --> 23:48.120
"I am the law. The law is me.
I wear the white hat."

23:48.120 --> 23:50.120
He's gone.
-Don't do that! Don't! Not now.

23:50.120 --> 23:52.540
There will be a time for it,
but this is not that time!

23:52.540 --> 23:53.880
Abby.

23:53.880 --> 23:55.120
Don't touch me!

23:55.120 --> 23:57.290
No one look at me,
no one touch me.

23:57.290 --> 23:59.080
[ Voice breaking ]
Don't cry or I will start

23:59.080 --> 24:01.670
and won't be able
to stop.

24:01.670 --> 24:03.750
Right now, it's time
to do something.

24:03.750 --> 24:05.040
Act now, cry later.

24:07.460 --> 24:09.040
[ Quietly ]
I'll take care of it.

24:09.040 --> 24:10.750
No! No more blood.

24:10.750 --> 24:13.210
If David is gone, then
we're the good guys now.

24:13.210 --> 24:16.540
We're the only
white hats left.

24:20.460 --> 24:22.040
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

24:22.040 --> 24:23.670
Just get us out.

24:23.670 --> 24:25.710
A new city, an island,
a fishing hut in Zanzibar --

24:25.710 --> 24:28.120
It doesn't matter as long as
it's far, far away from here.

24:28.120 --> 24:29.920
What am I,
a travel agency?!

24:29.920 --> 24:32.250
[ Whispering ]
Shh, keep your voice down.

24:32.250 --> 24:34.380
Look, you have
the resources.

24:34.380 --> 24:36.380
Just please --
-[ Whispering ] Please what?

24:36.380 --> 24:38.620
Risk my own freedom?
You and your husband

24:38.620 --> 24:41.420
would be the most-wanted
fugitive in America.
Shh.

24:41.420 --> 24:44.080
They find you, they follow
the trail, and it leads to me.

24:44.080 --> 24:46.500
Look, I am going to
prison...forever.

24:46.500 --> 24:49.540
Do you really want Robin
to grow up without parents?

24:49.540 --> 24:52.750
You blindly, stupidly
followed my daughter

24:52.750 --> 24:56.170
out of the trenches
and into the firing line.

24:56.170 --> 24:57.960
Now, what happens to you,
to your family

24:57.960 --> 25:00.330
is not my responsibility.

25:00.330 --> 25:03.960
I...am retired --
responsible only to me.

25:05.790 --> 25:08.960
Well, all I have now...

25:08.960 --> 25:11.250
all I am...

25:11.250 --> 25:13.750
is a parent.

25:13.750 --> 25:15.880
I can't retire.

25:20.170 --> 25:21.960
I wish you
the best of luck.

25:25.500 --> 25:27.170
[ Scoffs ]

25:32.380 --> 25:35.620
[ Door opens, closes ]

25:40.620 --> 25:42.420
Well, here's to losing.

25:42.420 --> 25:44.460
-No.
-We lost, Fitz.

25:44.460 --> 25:46.710
Cyrus does not get to
just walk away from this.

25:46.710 --> 25:48.670
[ Glass clunks ]
-If David were still alive,

25:48.670 --> 25:50.620
he would have
made certain

25:50.620 --> 25:52.960
that Cyrus didn't get to
just walk away from this.

25:52.960 --> 25:56.040
But Cyrus...

25:56.040 --> 25:58.040
he's got the Deputy AG
in his pocket,

25:58.040 --> 26:00.420
which means that Mellie
is going to be impeached,

26:00.420 --> 26:02.880
which means we are
all going to jail,

26:02.880 --> 26:06.170
which means that Cyrus didn't
get to just walk from this.

26:06.170 --> 26:07.920
You're right.
He also gets the Oval.

26:07.920 --> 26:09.580
-Well, we need to make sure th--
-Why?!

26:09.580 --> 26:12.210
Why did I even begin to think
that I could fix any of this,

26:12.210 --> 26:14.000
or anything at all?!

26:15.750 --> 26:17.460
My father was right.

26:17.460 --> 26:19.540
You think I'm the one
who's always right. No.

26:21.460 --> 26:23.500
Olivia...

26:23.500 --> 26:25.210
you're grieving.
-And?!

26:25.210 --> 26:26.710
And you're not
thinking clearly.

26:26.710 --> 26:28.580
My thoughts have
never been more clear.

26:28.580 --> 26:30.080
I didn't fix anything here,
Fitz.

26:30.080 --> 26:31.210
I just made it worse.

26:31.210 --> 26:32.580
By doing what's right?

26:32.580 --> 26:34.000
Come on.

26:34.000 --> 26:36.540
You have to know that.

26:36.540 --> 26:39.000
Tell me you know
you did the right thing.

26:39.000 --> 26:40.580
Will you stop saying that?!

26:40.580 --> 26:43.380
I am so sick of -- Who the hell
knows what's right?!

26:43.380 --> 26:46.880
I managed to take down every
single person I care about.

26:46.880 --> 26:48.540
Is that supposed to be
what's right?

26:48.540 --> 26:49.540
That's not what --

26:49.540 --> 26:50.670
I dragged everyone
down with me!

26:50.670 --> 26:52.330
Was that really
the right thing to do?

26:52.330 --> 26:53.880
Everybody did what they did
on their own!

26:53.880 --> 26:56.500
I destroyed a legacy
you spent a lifetime forging.

26:56.500 --> 26:58.670
I did that, not you.
I did that willingly.

26:58.670 --> 27:00.000
You didn't have a choice.

27:00.000 --> 27:01.460
I went over that cliff
with you.

27:01.460 --> 27:03.420
-And you made a mistake.
-How can you say that?

27:03.420 --> 27:05.790
Because I was the problem!

27:05.790 --> 27:09.290
♪♪

27:09.290 --> 27:13.170
♪♪

27:13.170 --> 27:14.830
[ Sniffles ]

27:14.830 --> 27:17.040
You followed me,

27:17.040 --> 27:19.710
you relied on me,
you trusted me

27:19.710 --> 27:23.380
when this entire time,
I was the problem.

27:23.380 --> 27:26.330
It was me.

27:26.330 --> 27:30.120
That's how it's always been.
It's been me.

27:30.120 --> 27:31.710
I realize that now.

27:33.330 --> 27:35.960
-You're not f--
-Stop.

27:35.960 --> 27:38.960
Before you say anything else,
before you try to argue with me

27:38.960 --> 27:41.330
any more than you
already have...

27:41.330 --> 27:44.290
I'd like you stop
and realize something.

27:45.620 --> 27:48.500
[ Sniffles ]
I'm going to jail tomorrow.

27:48.500 --> 27:54.040
♪♪

27:54.040 --> 27:56.830
This is, most likely,

27:56.830 --> 28:02.040
the very last time
that you and I...

28:02.040 --> 28:06.920
will ever be in the same room
together...alone.

28:06.920 --> 28:08.790
So we have
a choice to make.

28:08.790 --> 28:11.040
We can keep talking,

28:11.040 --> 28:12.580
we can keep having feelings...

28:12.580 --> 28:16.920
or...

28:16.920 --> 28:18.830
or we can do
something else.

28:18.830 --> 28:20.580
[ Sighs ]

28:20.580 --> 28:22.880
♪♪

28:22.880 --> 28:25.330
Feelings, option "A,"
something else, option "B."

28:25.330 --> 28:27.670
Which is it going to be?

28:27.670 --> 28:29.710
-Liv --
-Make a choice.

28:29.710 --> 28:32.580
Option "A"
or option "B"?

28:32.580 --> 28:34.670
"A" or "B"?

28:34.670 --> 28:35.790
[ Strongly ]
"A" or "B"?

28:35.790 --> 28:37.080
[ Chuckles ]

28:37.080 --> 28:39.120
"A" or "B."
"A" or "B"!

28:39.120 --> 28:41.120
-Olivia --
-Pick one!

28:41.120 --> 28:46.830
♪♪

28:46.830 --> 28:52.880
♪♪

28:53.580 --> 28:55.580
Take off your clothes.

28:55.580 --> 28:59.710
♪♪

28:59.710 --> 29:04.210
♪♪

29:04.210 --> 29:08.620
♪♪

29:08.620 --> 29:13.290
♪♪

29:19.170 --> 29:20.380
Reporter:
Washington is reacting today

29:20.380 --> 29:21.620
to the death
of Attorney General

29:21.620 --> 29:22.960
of the United States,
David Rosen.

29:22.960 --> 29:24.330
The coroner stated
that Rosen,

29:24.330 --> 29:26.040
the second-youngest AG
in the nation's history,

29:26.040 --> 29:27.670
suffered a massive coronary
last night

29:27.670 --> 29:30.210
at the home of Vice President
Cyrus Beene.

29:30.210 --> 29:33.080
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

29:37.330 --> 29:40.250
Fitz: I don't understand.
When did this happen?

29:40.250 --> 29:43.540
Okay. Thanks
for letting me know.

29:46.880 --> 29:48.750
What is it?

29:48.750 --> 29:50.330
Did the committee make
their recommendations?

29:50.330 --> 29:52.000
No.

29:52.000 --> 29:54.290
They've postponed.

29:54.290 --> 29:56.250
Postponed? Why?

29:56.250 --> 29:58.580
They have a new witness.

29:58.580 --> 30:00.880
♪♪

30:00.880 --> 30:04.170
[ Camera shutter clicking ]

30:04.170 --> 30:06.920
Mr. Pope, moments ago,
you stated that you --

30:06.920 --> 30:08.210
-Rowan.
-I'm sorry?

30:08.210 --> 30:10.790
Eli Pope is a civilian.

30:10.790 --> 30:13.170
I'm not speaking before
this committee as a civilian.

30:13.170 --> 30:15.790
I'm speaking before this
committee as Command of B613.

30:15.790 --> 30:19.710
As Command, I am Rowan.

30:19.710 --> 30:21.920
Apologies.

30:21.920 --> 30:24.250
"Rowan"
